Class DetectionResult

java.lang.Object
model.DetectionResult
public final class DetectionResult extends Object
Represents recognition results of an image.

A DetectionResult contains the image that was analyzed, a list of detected labels with their confidence scores, and the timestamp when the detection was performed. Labels can be added to the result after creation, but the result itself is immutable once fully constructed (except for label additions).

Version:
1.0
Author:
VisionTagger Team

  • Constructor Details

    • DetectionResult

      public DetectionResult(Image image)
      Constructs a DetectionResult for the given image.

      The detection timestamp is automatically set to the current time, and the labels list is initialized as empty. Labels should be added using addLabel().

      Parameters:
      image - the image that was analyzed (must not be null)
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if image is null

    • getLabels

      public List<Label> getLabels()
      Returns an unmodifiable list of labels to preserve immutability.

      The returned list is a read-only view of the internal labels list. To add labels, use the addLabel() method.

      Returns:
      an unmodifiable list of Label objects

    • getTopLabel

      public Label getTopLabel()
      Returns the label with the highest confidence score.

      If multiple labels have the same highest confidence, one of them is returned (the choice is non-deterministic). If no labels exist, returns null.

      Returns:
      the Label with the highest confidence, or null if the labels list is empty
